<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWilliams.2C_Kristian2006">Williams, Kristian (2006). <i>American methods: torture and the logic of domination</i>. Boston: South End Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0896087530" class="internal">ISBN 0-89608-753-0</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=American+methods%3A+torture+and+the+logic+of+domination&amp;rft.aulast=Williams%2C+Kristian&amp;rft.au=Williams%2C+Kristian&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.place=Boston&amp;rft.pub=South+End+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-89608-753-0&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<p><a name="References" id="References"></a></p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
<div class="references-small references-column-width" style="-moz-column-width:30em; column-width:30em;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-EbanVanityFairWB1-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-EbanVanityFairWB1_0-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFEban2007">Eban, Katherine (July 17, 2007). <a href="http://www.vanityfair.com/politics/features/2007/07/torture200707" class="external text" title="http://www.vanityfair.com/politics/features/2007/07/torture200707" rel="nofollow">"Rorschach and Awe"</a>. Vanity Fair<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.vanityfair.com/politics/features/2007/07/torture200707" class="external free" title="http://www.vanityfair.com/politics/features/2007/07/torture200707" rel="nofollow">http://www.vanityfair.com/politics/features/2007/07/torture200707</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-17</span>.  "It was terrifying," military psychologist Bryce Lefever is quoted as saying, "...you're strapped to an inclined gurney and you're in four-point restraint, your head is almost immobilized, and they pour water between your nose and your mouth, so if you're likely to breathe, you're going to get a lot of water. You go into an oxygen panic."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Rorschach+and+Awe&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Eban&amp;rft.aufirst=Katherine&amp;rft.au=Eban%2C+Katherine&amp;rft.date=July+17%2C+2007&amp;rft.pub=Vanity+Fair&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.vanityfair.com%2Fpolitics%2Ffeatures%2F2007%2F07%2Ftorture200707&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> Waterboarding is considered to be torture by a wide range of authorities, including legal experts, politicians, war veterans, intelligence officials, military judges, and human rights organizations (See <a href="/wiki/Waterboarding#Classification_as_torture" title="Waterboarding">Classification as torture</a> for more information). In the United States in recent years, arguments have been put forward that waterboarding might not be torture in all cases after it was revealed that this technique was used to interrogate suspects in relation to the <a href="/wiki/War_on_terror" title="War on terror" class="mw-redirect">war on terror</a> (See <a href="/wiki/Waterboarding#Controversy_over_classification_as_torture_in_the_United_States" title="Waterboarding">Controversy over classification in the United States</a> for more information).</li>
<li id="cite_note-WhiteWAPostWB_110807-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-WhiteWAPostWB_110807_2-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFWhite2007">White, Josh (November 8, 2007). <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/11/08/AR2007110802150.html" class="external text" title="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/11/08/AR2007110802150.html" rel="nofollow">"Waterboarding Is Torture, Says Ex-Navy Instructor"</a>. Washington Post<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/11/08/AR2007110802150.html" class="external free" title="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/11/08/AR2007110802150.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/11/08/AR2007110802150.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-17</span>.  "As the event unfolded, I was fully conscious of what was happening: I was being tortured."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Waterboarding+Is+Torture%2C+Says+Ex-Navy+Instructor&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=White&amp;rft.aufirst=Josh&amp;rft.au=White%2C+Josh&amp;rft.date=November+8%2C+2007&amp;rft.pub=Washington+Post&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fwp-dyn%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2F2007%2F11%2F08%2FAR2007110802150.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-HRW_open_letter_WB-3">^ <a href="#cite_ref-HRW_open_letter_WB_3-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-HRW_open_letter_WB_3-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-HRW_open_letter_WB_3-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-HRW_open_letter_WB_3-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFVarious2006">Various (April 5, 2006). <a href="http://hrw.org/english/docs/2006/04/06/usdom13130.htm" class="external text" title="http://hrw.org/english/docs/2006/04/06/usdom13130.htm" rel="nofollow">"Open Letter to Attorney General Alberto Gonzales"</a>. <i>Human Rights News</i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://hrw.org/english/docs/2006/04/06/usdom13130.htm" class="external free" title="http://hrw.org/english/docs/2006/04/06/usdom13130.htm" rel="nofollow">http://hrw.org/english/docs/2006/04/06/usdom13130.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-18</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Open+Letter+to+Attorney+General+Alberto+Gonzales&amp;rft.atitle=Human+Rights+News&amp;rft.aulast=Various&amp;rft.au=Various&amp;rft.date=April+5%2C+2006&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fhrw.org%2Fenglish%2Fdocs%2F2006%2F04%2F06%2Fusdom13130.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> In a letter to Attorney General Alberto Gonzales more than 100 United States law professors stated unequivocally that waterboarding is torture, and the use of the practice is a criminal felony punishable under the U.S. federal criminal code.</li>
<li id="cite_note-JuristPittWB_100807-4">^ <a href="#cite_ref-JuristPittWB_100807_4-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JuristPittWB_100807_4-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFDavis2007">Davis, Benjamin (2007-10-08). <a href="http://jurist.law.pitt.edu/forumy/2007/10/endgame-on-torture-time-to-call-bluff.php" class="external text" title="http://jurist.law.pitt.edu/forumy/2007/10/endgame-on-torture-time-to-call-bluff.php" rel="nofollow">"Endgame on Torture: Time to Call the Bluff"</a>. <a href="/wiki/University_of_Pittsburgh" title="University of Pittsburgh">University of Pittsburgh</a> School of Law<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://jurist.law.pitt.edu/forumy/2007/10/endgame-on-torture-time-to-call-bluff.php" class="external free" title="http://jurist.law.pitt.edu/forumy/2007/10/endgame-on-torture-time-to-call-bluff.php" rel="nofollow">http://jurist.law.pitt.edu/forumy/2007/10/endgame-on-torture-time-to-call-bluff.php</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-18</span>.  "Waterboarding has been torture for at least 500&#160;years. All of us know that torture is going on."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Endgame+on+Torture%3A+Time+to+Call+the+Bluff&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Davis&amp;rft.aufirst=Benjamin&amp;rft.au=Davis%2C+Benjamin&amp;rft.date=2007-10-08&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BUniversity+of+Pittsburgh%5D%5D+School+of+Law&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fjurist.law.pitt.edu%2Fforumy%2F2007%2F10%2Fendgame-on-torture-time-to-call-bluff.php&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-DN.21_WB_110507-5">^ <a href="#cite_ref-DN.21_WB_110507_5-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-DN.21_WB_110507_5-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-DN.21_WB_110507_5-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news"><a href="http://www.democracynow.org/2007/11/5/french_journalist_henri_alleg_describes_his" class="external text" title="http://www.democracynow.org/2007/11/5/french_journalist_henri_alleg_describes_his" rel="nofollow">"French Journalist Henri Alleg Describes His Torture Being Waterboarded by French Forces During Algerian War"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Democracy_Now!" title="Democracy Now!">Democracy Now!</a>. 2007-11-05<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.democracynow.org/2007/11/5/french_journalist_henri_alleg_describes_his" class="external free" title="http://www.democracynow.org/2007/11/5/french_journalist_henri_alleg_describes_his" rel="nofollow">http://www.democracynow.org/2007/11/5/french_journalist_henri_alleg_describes_his</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-18</span>.  "I have described the waterboarding I was submitted to. And no one can say, having passed through it, that this was not torture, especially when he has endured other types of torture—burning, electricity and beating, and so on."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=French+Journalist+Henri+Alleg+Describes+His+Torture+Being+Waterboarded+by+French+Forces+During+Algerian+War&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2007-11-05&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BDemocracy+Now%21%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.democracynow.org%2F2007%2F11%2F5%2Ffrench_journalist_henri_alleg_describes_his&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-NW_WB_110507-6">^ <a href="#cite_ref-NW_WB_110507_6-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-NW_WB_110507_6-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-NW_WB_110507_6-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news"><a href="http://msnbc.msn.com/id/10019179/site/newsweek/page/2/" class="external text" title="http://msnbc.msn.com/id/10019179/site/newsweek/page/2/" rel="nofollow">"Torture's Terrible Toll"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Newsweek" title="Newsweek">Newsweek</a>. 2005-11-21<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://msnbc.msn.com/id/10019179/site/newsweek/page/2/" class="external free" title="http://msnbc.msn.com/id/10019179/site/newsweek/page/2/" rel="nofollow">http://msnbc.msn.com/id/10019179/site/newsweek/page/2/</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Torture%27s+Terrible+Toll&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2005-11-21&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BNewsweek%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fmsnbc.msn.com%2Fid%2F10019179%2Fsite%2Fnewsweek%2Fpage%2F2%2F&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>According to Republican <a href="/wiki/United_States_Senator" title="United States Senator" class="mw-redirect">United States Senator</a> and 2008 presidential candidate <a href="/wiki/John_McCain" title="John McCain">John McCain</a>, who was tortured as a <a href="/wiki/Prisoner_of_war" title="Prisoner of war">prisoner of war</a> in <a href="/wiki/North_Vietnam" title="North Vietnam">North Vietnam</a>, waterboarding is "torture, no different than holding a pistol to his head and firing a blank" and can damage the subject's psyche "in ways that may never heal."</li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFGrey2009">Grey, Stephen (2006). <i>Ghost Plane: The True Story of the CIA Torture Program</i>. New York, New York: St. Martin's Press. pp.&#160;225–226.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Ghost+Plane%3A+The+True+Story+of+the+CIA+Torture+Program&amp;rft.aulast=Grey&amp;rft.aufirst=Stephen&amp;rft.au=Grey%2C+Stephen&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B225%E2%80%93226&amp;rft.place=New+York%2C+New+York&amp;rft.pub=St.+Martin%27s+Press&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> A former senior official in the directorate of operations is quoted (in full) as saying: "'Of course it was torture. Try it and you'll see.'" Another "former higher-up in the directorate of operations" said "'Yes, it's torture'".</li>
<li id="cite_note-CaL_WB_110507-8">^ <a href="#cite_ref-CaL_WB_110507_8-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-CaL_WB_110507_8-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFBell2007">Bell, Nicole (2007-11-03). <a href="http://www.crooksandliars.com/2007/11/03/retired-jags-send-letter-to-leahy-waterboarding-is-inhumane-it-is-torture-and-it-is-illegal/" class="external text" title="http://www.crooksandliars.com/2007/11/03/retired-jags-send-letter-to-leahy-waterboarding-is-inhumane-it-is-torture-and-it-is-illegal/" rel="nofollow">"Retired JAGs Send Letter To Leahy: “Waterboarding is inhumane, it is torture, and it is illegal.”"</a>. Crooks and Liars<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.crooksandliars.com/2007/11/03/retired-jags-send-letter-to-leahy-waterboarding-is-inhumane-it-is-torture-and-it-is-illegal/" class="external free" title="http://www.crooksandliars.com/2007/11/03/retired-jags-send-letter-to-leahy-waterboarding-is-inhumane-it-is-torture-and-it-is-illegal/" rel="nofollow">http://www.crooksandliars.com/2007/11/03/retired-jags-send-letter-to-leahy-waterboarding-is-inhumane-it-is-torture-and-it-is-illegal/</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-18</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Retired+JAGs+Send+Letter+To+Leahy%3A+%E2%80%9CWaterboarding+is+inhumane%2C+it+is+torture%2C+and+it+is+illegal.%E2%80%9D&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Bell&amp;rft.aufirst=Nicole&amp;rft.au=Bell%2C+Nicole&amp;rft.date=2007-11-03&amp;rft.pub=Crooks+and+Liars&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.crooksandliars.com%2F2007%2F11%2F03%2Fretired-jags-send-letter-to-leahy-waterboarding-is-inhumane-it-is-torture-and-it-is-illegal%2F&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> "Waterboarding is inhumane, it is torture, and it is illegal." and "Waterboarding detainees amounts to illegal torture in all circumstances.". From Rear Admiral Donald J. Guter, United States Navy (Ret.) Judge Advocate General of the Navy, 2000-02; Rear Admiral John D. Hutson, United States Navy (Ret.) Judge Advocate General of the Navy, 1997-2000; Major General John L. Fugh, United States Army (Ret.) Judge Advocate General of the Army, 1991-93; Brigadier General David M. Brahms, United States Marine Corps (Ret.) Staff Judge Advocate to the Commandant, 1985-88.</li>
<li id="cite_note-HRW_WB_110507-9">^ <a href="#cite_ref-HRW_WB_110507_9-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-HRW_WB_110507_9-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-HRW_WB_110507_9-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news"><a href="http://hrw.org/english/docs/2005/11/21/usdom12069.htm" class="external text" title="http://hrw.org/english/docs/2005/11/21/usdom12069.htm" rel="nofollow">"CIA Whitewashing Torture"</a>. Human Rights Watch. 2005-11-21<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://hrw.org/english/docs/2005/11/21/usdom12069.htm" class="external free" title="http://hrw.org/english/docs/2005/11/21/usdom12069.htm" rel="nofollow">http://hrw.org/english/docs/2005/11/21/usdom12069.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-18</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=CIA+Whitewashing+Torture&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2005-11-21&amp;rft.pub=Human+Rights+Watch&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fhrw.org%2Fenglish%2Fdocs%2F2005%2F11%2F21%2Fusdom12069.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>"There is no doubt that waterboarding is torture, despite the administration’s reluctance to say so,” Kenneth Roth, executive director of Human Rights Watch.</li>
<li id="cite_note-AI_WB_102607-10">^ <a href="#cite_ref-AI_WB_102607_10-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-AI_WB_102607_10-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news"><a href="http://www.amnestyusa.org/document.php?lang=e&amp;id=ENGUSA20061026002" class="external text" title="http://www.amnestyusa.org/document.php?lang=e&amp;id=ENGUSA20061026002" rel="nofollow">"Amnesty International Response to Cheney's "No-Brainer" Comment"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Amnesty_International" title="Amnesty International">Amnesty International</a>. 2006-10-26<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.amnestyusa.org/document.php?lang=e&amp;id=ENGUSA20061026002" class="external free" title="http://www.amnestyusa.org/document.php?lang=e&amp;id=ENGUSA20061026002" rel="nofollow">http://www.amnestyusa.org/document.php?lang=e&amp;id=ENGUSA20061026002</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-18</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Amnesty+International+Response+to+Cheney%27s+%22No-Brainer%22+Comment&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2006-10-26&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BAmnesty+International%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnestyusa.org%2Fdocument.php%3Flang%3De%26id%3DENGUSA20061026002&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-NYTimesWB_110707-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-NYTimesWB_110707_11-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFShane2007">Shane, Scott (2007-11-07). <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2007/11/07/us/07waterboard.html?_r=1&amp;oref=slogin" class="external text" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2007/11/07/us/07waterboard.html?_r=1&amp;oref=slogin" rel="nofollow">"A Firsthand Experience Before Decision on Torture"</a>. New York Times<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2007/11/07/us/07waterboard.html?_r=1&amp;oref=slogin" class="external free" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2007/11/07/us/07waterboard.html?_r=1&amp;oref=slogin" rel="nofollow">http://www.nytimes.com/2007/11/07/us/07waterboard.html?_r=1&amp;oref=slogin</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-18</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=A+Firsthand+Experience+Before+Decision+on+Torture&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Shane&amp;rft.aufirst=Scott&amp;rft.au=Shane%2C+Scott&amp;rft.date=2007-11-07&amp;rft.pub=New+York+Times&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2007%2F11%2F07%2Fus%2F07waterboard.html%3F_r%3D1%26oref%3Dslogin&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
