<li id="cite_note-NY-13">^ <a href="#cite_ref-NY_13-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-NY_13-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFMayer2005">Mayer, Jane (2005-02-14). <a href="http://www.newyorker.com/archive/2005/02/14/050214fa_fact6" class="external text" title="http://www.newyorker.com/archive/2005/02/14/050214fa_fact6" rel="nofollow">"Outsourcing Torture"</a>. The New Yorker<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.newyorker.com/archive/2005/02/14/050214fa_fact6" class="external free" title="http://www.newyorker.com/archive/2005/02/14/050214fa_fact6" rel="nofollow">http://www.newyorker.com/archive/2005/02/14/050214fa_fact6</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-18</span>.  "Dr. Allen Keller, the director of the Bellevue/N.Y.U. Program for Survivors of Torture, told me that he had treated a number of people who had been subjected to such forms of near-asphyxiation, and he argued that it was indeed torture. Some victims were still traumatized years later, he said."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Outsourcing+Torture&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Mayer&amp;rft.aufirst=Jane&amp;rft.au=Mayer%2C+Jane&amp;rft.date=2005-02-14&amp;rft.pub=The+New+Yorker&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Farchive%2F2005%2F02%2F14%2F050214fa_fact6&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
