<li id="cite_note-Safire-26">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Safire_26-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Safire_26-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Safire_26-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Safire_26-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Safire_26-4" title=""><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFSafire2008"><a href="/wiki/William_Safire" title="William Safire">Safire, William</a> (March 9, 2008). <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/03/09/magazine/09wwlnSafire-t.html?pagewanted=print" class="external text" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/03/09/magazine/09wwlnSafire-t.html?pagewanted=print" rel="nofollow">"On Language: Waterboarding"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_New_York_Times" title="The New York Times">The New York Times</a></i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/03/09/magazine/09wwlnSafire-t.html?pagewanted=print" class="external free" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/03/09/magazine/09wwlnSafire-t.html?pagewanted=print" rel="nofollow">http://www.nytimes.com/2008/03/09/magazine/09wwlnSafire-t.html?pagewanted=print</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-07-08</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=On+Language%3A+Waterboarding&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Safire&amp;rft.aufirst=William&amp;rft.au=Safire%2C+William&amp;rft.date=March+9%2C+2008&amp;rft.pub=%27%27%5B%5BThe+New+York+Times%5D%5D%27%27&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2008%2F03%2F09%2Fmagazine%2F09wwlnSafire-t.html%3Fpagewanted%3Dprint&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
