<li id="cite_note-30"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFGrey2009">Grey, Stephen (2006). <i>Ghost Plane: The True Story of the CIA Torture Program</i>. New York, New York: St. Martin's Press. pp.&#160;225–226.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Ghost+Plane%3A+The+True+Story+of+the+CIA+Torture+Program&amp;rft.aulast=Grey&amp;rft.aufirst=Stephen&amp;rft.au=Grey%2C+Stephen&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B225%E2%80%93226&amp;rft.place=New+York%2C+New+York&amp;rft.pub=St.+Martin%27s+Press&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> A former senior official in the directorate of operations is quoted (in full) as saying: "'Of course it was torture. Try it and you'll see.'" Another "former higher-up in the directorate of operations" said "'Yes, it's torture'".</li>
