<li id="cite_note-wp-64">^ <a href="#cite_ref-wp_64-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-wp_64-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-wp_64-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFEvan_Wallach2007">Evan Wallach (2007-11-02). <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/11/02/AR2007110201170.html" class="external text" title="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/11/02/AR2007110201170.html" rel="nofollow">"Waterboarding Used to Be a Crime"</a>. Washington Post<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/11/02/AR2007110201170.html" class="external free" title="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/11/02/AR2007110201170.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/11/02/AR2007110201170.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Waterboarding+Used+to+Be+a+Crime&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Evan+Wallach&amp;rft.au=Evan+Wallach&amp;rft.date=2007-11-02&amp;rft.pub=Washington+Post&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fwp-dyn%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2F2007%2F11%2F02%2FAR2007110201170.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Waterboarding"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
