<li id="cite_note-Sheldon_Whitehouse-147"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Sheldon_Whitehouse_147-0" title="">^</a></b> Investigation by Justice Department
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/02/23/washington/23justice.html?_r=1&amp;sq=&amp;st=nyt&amp;adxnnl=1&amp;oref=slogin&amp;scp=2&amp;adxnnlx=1203948910-L6zJ6TMfrAyXqXZczt9Q3g" class="external text" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/02/23/washington/23justice.html?_r=1&amp;sq=&amp;st=nyt&amp;adxnnl=1&amp;oref=slogin&amp;scp=2&amp;adxnnlx=1203948910-L6zJ6TMfrAyXqXZczt9Q3g" rel="nofollow">Waterboarding Focus of Inquiry by Justice Dept.</a> Scott Shane, New York Times, February 23, 2008</li>
<li><a href="http://whitehouse.senate.gov/record.cfm?id=293379&amp;" class="external text" title="http://whitehouse.senate.gov/record.cfm?id=293379&amp;" rel="nofollow">Durbin and Whitehouse: Justice Department is Investigating Torture Authorization - Senate Judiciary Democrats Called for Inquiry into DOJ's Role in Overseeing CIA's Use of Waterboarding</a> Press Release of Senator Whitehouse, February 22, 2008</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-148"><b><a href="#cite_ref-148" title="">^</a></b> Dan Eggen, <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/03/08/AR2008030800304.html" class="external text" title="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/03/08/AR2008030800304.html" rel="nofollow">"Bush Announces Veto of Waterboarding Ban,"</a> <i>Washington Post</i>, Mar. 8, 2008.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Bush_vetoed-149"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Bush_vetoed_149-0" title="">^</a></b> *<a href="http://www.reuters.com/article/topNews/idUSN0736443620080308" class="external text" title="http://www.reuters.com/article/topNews/idUSN0736443620080308" rel="nofollow">Bush vetoes bill outlawing CIA waterboarding</a> Richard Cowan with Eric Beech, <i>Reuters</i>, March 8, 2008</li>
<li id="cite_note-Waterboarding_Banned-150"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Waterboarding_Banned_150-0" title="">^</a></b> [<a href="http://www.cnn.com/2009/POLITICS/01/22/obama.interrogations/" class="external free" title="http://www.cnn.com/2009/POLITICS/01/22/obama.interrogations/" rel="nofollow">http://www.cnn.com/2009/POLITICS/01/22/obama.interrogations/</a>&gt;</li>
</ol>
</div>
